\ Memory-safety test. Only runs when the engine was compiled with
\ FF_SAFE_MEM=ON; the default build segfaults on the bad fetch and
\ takes the test driver down with it.
\
\ The driver feeds the entire file to one ff_eval call. The bad
\ op below raises FF_ERR_BAD_PTR via vtracef -- which the driver
\ ignores -- and ff_eval returns early. Anything after the bad op
\ is silently skipped, so the expected stdout is just the sentinel
\ printed before.

42 .

\ everything below would segfault under the default build:

0 @ drop
1 c@ drop
0 0 !
99 execute
0 evaluate drop

\ never reached:

99 .
